content:
 I found this awesome cut-up poetry generator, which takes the text of famous poets and builds structured poetry out of it. The guy that made it even developed the underlying algorithm as a research project. I have put a version of a free Amazon EC2 instance, wrote a little twitter bot in node.js, and wired the poetry generator with the twitter bot, and now I have this: https://twitter.com/haikumachine - a twitter bot that posts a haiku every five minutes, derived from Dylan Thomas&rsquo;s poetry.
It could be improved, and there are sometimes erroneous tweets where the syllables aren&rsquo;t counted quite right, or some of the punctuation doesn&rsquo;t make sense once cut up, but damnit, it&rsquo;s a bot that writes Haikus.
&ldquo;The grains beyond age / Oh miracle of fishes / in the lamb white days&rdquo;
— I am a Haiku Machine (@haikumachine) July 26, 2013
//platform.twitter.com/widgets.js

